<exercise id="fs-id1166167085032">
<problem id="fs-id1166167085034">
<para id="fs-id1166167085036">A long, straight wire of radius <emphasis effect="italics">R</emphasis> carries a current <emphasis effect="italics">I</emphasis> that is distributed uniformly over the cross-section of the wire. At what distance from the axis of the wire is the magnitude of the magnetic field a maximum?</para>
